<!-- Handling depression -->
<category>
    <pattern>I FEEL DEPRESSED</pattern>
    <template>
        <set name="mood">depressed</set>
        I hear you, and I want you to know that your feelings are valid. Here's something that might help:
        
        üå± Remember: Depression lies. You are:
        - Stronger than you know
        - Worthy of happiness
        - Not alone in this journey
        - Capable of getting through this
        
        Would you like to:
        1. Read an uplifting story
        2. Try a mood-lifting activity
        3. Learn about positive habits
        4. Hear what helped others
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Mood-lifting activities -->
<category>
    <pattern>MOOD LIFTING ACTIVITIES</pattern>
    <template>
        Let's try these proven mood-boosters:
        
        1. The 5-4-3-2-1 Grounding Exercise:
        - Name 5 things you can see
        - 4 things you can touch
        - 3 things you can hear
        - 2 things you can smell
        - 1 thing you can taste
        
        2. Joy List Creation:
        Write down 3 tiny things that brought you joy before
        
        3. Movement Magic:
        Even a 5-minute dance to your favorite song can help
        
        Which would you like to try first?
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Positive habits -->
<category>
    <pattern>TEACH ME POSITIVE HABITS</pattern>
    <template>
        Here are life-changing positive habits:
        
        üåÖ Morning Routine:
        - Wake up at the same time
        - Drink water first thing
        - 5 minutes of stretching
        - Say one positive affirmation
        
        üåô Evening Routine:
        - Reflect on 3 good things
        - Light exercise or yoga
        - Digital sunset (reduce screen time)
        - Relaxing bedtime ritual
        
        Would you like to learn more about any of these habits?
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Gratitude practice -->
<category>
    <pattern>LETS PRACTICE GRATITUDE</pattern>
    <template>
        Let's do a simple gratitude exercise:
        
        Complete these sentences:
        1. Today I'm grateful for...
        2. Something good that happened recently...
        3. Someone I appreciate in my life...
        
        Remember: Gratitude can rewire our brain for happiness!
    </template>
</category>

